<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-12T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-12T04:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">792.94/57: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-12T18:00:00+09:00">June 12, 1940—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 12—3:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>443. It was announced today at the Foreign Office that a treaty was
                            signed at Tokyo this morning with Thailand containing the following
                            provisions: <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Mutual respect for the territory of the other;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Exchange of information on matters of mutual interest;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Each party to refrain from assisting any nation at war with
                                    other party.</item>
                            </list></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>